// ============================================================
// SECURITY GUIDELINES SUMMARY:
// ============================================================
//
// NEVER LOG:
//   - Authentication tokens (Bearer tokens, API keys, JWTs)
//   - Passwords or secrets
//   - Credit card numbers, CVVs
//   - Social Security Numbers (SSN) or national IDs
//   - Full request/response bodies (may contain PII)
//   - Database connection strings
//   - Session cookies
//   - Personal health information (PHI)
//
// ALWAYS LOG:
//   - Correlation IDs for request tracing
//   - Opaque user identifiers (not emails/names)
//   - Request metadata (method, path, content-length, status codes)
//   - Performance metrics (duration, timestamps)
//   - Error codes and types (not full stack traces in production)
//   - Business event identifiers (order IDs, product IDs)
//   - Sanitized/masked versions of identifiers when needed
//
// ADDITIONAL MEASURES:
//   - Use structured logging (ILogger with templates)
//   - Implement log levels appropriately (Debug vs Info vs Error)
//   - Configure log retention policies
//   - Use Application Insights with data sampling
//   - Enable log access auditing
//   - Review logs regularly for accidental PII exposure